    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Godetia bifrons are anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial. Its antiseptic property makes it useful for wound healing and preventing infection. The plant's antispasmodic property helps in reducing muscle spasms and alleviating pain, while its antioxidant property protects cells from oxidative damage caused by free radicals. Antimicrobial bioactive compounds such as flavonoids and saponins in Godetia bifrons are responsible for its therapeutic properties, including antiseptic and antimicrobial effects, which contribute to its wound healing and infection prevention properties. Volatile oils in the plant contribute to its antispasmodic and antioxidant properties, making it useful in reducing muscle spasms and protecting cells from oxidative damage.",
