    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Godetia bifrons are flavonoids, particularly kaempferol and quercetin, which have anti-inflammatory properties, and isoflavones, including genistein and daidzein, that exhibit antioxidant and immunomodulatory activities. The plant also contains iridoid glycosides, such as geniposide, which have been shown to have anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial effects. Additionally, Godetia bifrons contains phenolic acids, like caffeic acid and ferulic acid, that possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. The plant's bioactive compounds have been found to exert their healing effects through various mechanisms, including the inhibition of pro-inflammatory enzymes and the modulation of immune responses. These constituents work in concert to provide the plant's therapeutic benefits, making Godetia bifrons a valuable resource for the development of new medicines.",
