    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Godetia bifrons are made by utilizing its flowers, leaves, and roots. Tea is prepared by infusing the flowers in hot water to treat respiratory issues such as bronchitis and coughs. A tincture is created by extracting the plant's active compounds in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin, used to treat anxiety and insomnia. Infusions, made by steeping the plant's parts in hot water, are also used to treat digestive issues like diarrhea and constipation. Salves and infused oils are prepared by mixing the plant's extracts with a carrier oil, used topically to treat skin irritations and wounds.",
