    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Godetia bifrons improperly include causing diarrhea, which is likely due to the plant's high concentration of anthraquinone glycosides that can irritate the gastrointestinal tract. Inducing vomiting can also occur, as the plant's toxins can stimulate the vomiting center in the brain. Furthermore, Godetia bifrons may interact with medications, such as blood thinners and diabetes medications, by altering their metabolism or potency. Additionally, improper use of Godetia bifrons may lead to skin irritation, possibly due to the plant's allergenic compounds, which can cause redness, itching, and blistering. Allergic reactions, including anaphylaxis, can also be triggered by Godetia bifrons, particularly in individuals with pre-existing allergies, making it essential to handle and use the plant with caution.",
